A Kiambu legislator has asked the youth not to be used by politicians to cause violence during campaigns and after the election.Lari MP Mburu Kahangara said some structures and institutions were built many years ago and have helped many people, but can be destroyed in a very short time.He urged the youth to concentrate on what they do to earn a living. &ldquo;Young people must not be carried away by politicians to an extent of causing violence,&rdquo; Kahangara said.&ldquo;At times, some important institutions and facilities end up being vandalised. We must protect what we have achieved.&rdquo;He spoke at Kimende High School on Wednesday, when he accompanied NYS deputy director general Sam Muchuki, who commissioned youth programmes in the area. Also present was deputy county commissioner Aaron Koros.